                    <p class="info-text margin-btm-30">
                        When thinking about or setting up a marine tank, you need to think about what stock you would like to put in the tank.
                        Each type of animal has it's own needs. For example, are you want to go for a soft coral or hard coral dominant tank?
                        Each type of coral requires different things. Most hard corals require high light levels and steady water parameters,
                        whereas soft corals are much more tolerant to low light and variable water parameters.
                        <br /><br />
                        When selecting fish, care must be taken to select compatible fish. You would not want to put a small goby in with a
                        ferocious lion fish as it will be so long little goby. Likewise, you would not want to put a puffer fish in with other
                        fish in case it puffs out and poisons the water. Only certain fish can tolerate it's poison within an enclosed area.
                        <br /><br />
                        Use the fish stock calculator to work out how many fish you can have in a given tank size.
                    </p>
                </div>
               <div class="col-md-1></div>
